text: Janet Seidel (28 May 1955 - 8 August 2017) was an Australian singer, pianist and educator. She was born in Cummins, South Australia. Her albums, recorded with her brother bassist David Seidel, have been nominated for prizes such as the ARIA Music Awards. Her album Moon of Manakoora won the Bell Award for Best Australian Jazz Vocal Album in 2006. She was a music teacher at Sydney Girls High School. Seidel died on 8 August 2017 from ovarian cancer at her home in Sydney, New South Wales at the age of 62.Janet Seidel: The cabaret singer with the little-girl voice is gone ==References== Category:1955 births Category:2017 deaths Category:Deaths from ovarian cancer Category:Cancer deaths in Sydney Category:Australian singers Category:Australian musicians Category:Australian educators Category:Jazz pianists
